prompt:
Add a public function called GradeToLetter to Calculator.calr that converts a numeric grade (0-100) to a letter grade category. It takes i32 parameter grade and returns i32 (4 for A: 90+, 3 for B: 80-89, 2 for C: 70-79, 1 for D: 60-69, 0 for F: below 60).

Use nested if statements with unique IDs:
§F{f003:GradeToLetter:pub}
  §I{i32:grade}
  §O{i32}
  §Q (>= grade 0)
  §Q (<= grade 100)
  §IF{if001} (>= grade 90)
    §R 4
  §EL
    §IF{if002} (>= grade 80)
      §R 3
    §EL
      §IF{if003} (>= grade 70)
        §R 2
      §EL
        §IF{if004} (>= grade 60)
          §R 1
        §EL
          §R 0
        §/I{if004}
      §/I{if003}
    §/I{if002}
  §/I{if001}
§/F{f003}

Note: Each nested if block must have a unique ID (if001, if002, etc.). §EL (else) does not take an ID.
